{"title":"Angel’s Maxway Cycles Zephyrus Road Bike: Steel, Coffee, Clay – Daniel Yang","link":"https://theradavist.com/angels-maxway-cycles-zephyrus-road/","date":1748246423000,"content":"<p><em>Pride, passion, and performance: the <a href=\"https://www.maxway-cycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Zephyrus</a> is a steel road bike worthy of Maxway Cycles’ name. During <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/daniel-yang/\" target=\"_blank\">Daniel Yang</a>’s visit to the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/boutique-steel-bikes-taipei-cycle-show/\" target=\"_blank\">Taipei Cycle Show</a>, he had a chance to capture the image and story of this new bike.</em></p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>“Steel Bikes Are Low-End”</h3>\n<p>That comment lit a fire under Angel Chiu of Maxway, Taiwan’s best-known steel frame factory.</p>\n<p>In Western cycling, steel is cherished for its history, aesthetics, and ride quality. But in Asia, the scene pulls heavily from European trends and World Tour racing. In Taiwan, road cycling dominates, and imported carbon frames are the norm.</p>\n<p>Maxway wanted to prove that steel is still a modern, high-performance material. The result? One of the most beautiful bikes at the Taipei Cycle Show: the Zephyrus – a bike worthy of the Maxway name.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-31.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-31.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-31.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-31.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Maxway Zephyrus</h3>\n<p><em>“At last year’s Taipei Show, a friend’s friend came by the booth and said, ‘Oh, so you only make steel bikes? That’s why I’ve never seen them. Steel bikes are low-end.’</em></p>\n<p><em>I was honestly pretty mad. I wanted revenge. I wanted to show that steel can be more than just classic bikes. Steel can be high-performance.”</em><br />\n— Angel Chiu</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-3.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-3.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>There’s nothing more motivating than being underestimated. Angel channeled that energy into developing the Maxway Zephyrus – a modern steel road bike built with Columbus Life tubing. The frame weighs just 1.4 kg, and the complete bike comes in at 7.6 kg. It’s a true race bike: tight wheelbase, sharp handling, and fully internal cable routing.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-4.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-4.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-4.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-4.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-6.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-6.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-9.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-9.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The first challenge was fit. At just 5’1” (155 cm), Angel has always struggled to find a properly-sized road bike. One of the advantages of working with steel is that geometry is infinitely customizable. This allowed Angel to design a small frame with traditional aesthetics, paired with a 505 mm effective toptube, 460 mm seattube, and 150 mm cranks.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-18.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-18.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-8.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-8.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>While many assume lightweight steel bikes won’t pass ISO testing, this one does, thanks to expert welds and careful craftsmanship. Columbus Life tube butts are as thin as .4mm. Only Maxway’s most experienced welders work on this frame.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-21.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-21.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-21.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-21.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>This 54cm was built for her boyfriend Sam, a former pro racer who, like many, had only ridden carbon. After a few rides, he admitted he was surprised; the steel bike felt smooth, fast, and genuinely fun.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-16.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-16.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-19.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-19.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-20.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-20.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-20.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-20.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The Zephyrus will be available in two colorways, inspired by the landscape surrounding the Maxway factory: metallic green for the dense vegetation and cobalt blue for the water that fills the rice paddies. Both fade to silver, representing the material hiding under the paint.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-34.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-34.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-34.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-34.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-30.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-30.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-30.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-30.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-35.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-35.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-35.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-35.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>At first glance, I thought the green fade with the holographic Maxway logos felt dated, but the more I looked at it, the more it gave off a wholesome retro vibe, like a 90’s Pokemon card, in the best possible way. The graphics are an authentic representation of a factory that has been building frames for almost 40 years.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-36.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-36.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-36.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-36.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-37.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-37.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-37.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-37.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The Cobalt Blue frame also has a deeper meaning: Project C3.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-11.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-11.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-11.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-11.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-13.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-13.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/project_c3_?utm_source=ig_web_button_share_sheet&amp;igsh=ZDNlZDc0MzIxNw%3D%3D\" target=\"_blank\">Coffee Cycling Clay</a></h3>\n<p>Less than an hour’s ride from Maxway is Project C3 Cafe: Coffee, Cycling, Clay – a joint venture between Sam, Angel, and her sister, Amy. Project C3 is located in Zhuolan, a small town at the foothills of the mountains. To Angel, it’s more than a coffee shop; it’s a place for rest, self-reflection, and community.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-26.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-26.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Project C3 sits along a famous cycling road, known to locals as “Romantic Road Three”(浪漫台三線), which connects Taichung to the valleys and mountains Taiwan is famous for. They hope Project C3 will help grow the cycling community in Taiwan, and evolve the cafe into a riding destination. I didn’t have time to check it out on this trip, but it’s definitely on my radar now.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-28.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-28.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-28.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-28.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-25.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-25.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-25.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-25.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Availability</h3>\n<p>For Angel, the Zephyrus connects the pieces of her world: her passion for cycling, her family’s factory, and Project C3. For Maxway, it’s more than a show bike, it’s a statement: proof that metal bikes can be light, luxurious, and fast.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-22.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-22.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-22.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025_Angels_Maxway_C3-22.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>As a framebuilder, one of the happiest moments is spotting a beautiful bike in the distance and realizing you made it. I am glad a manufacturer gets to feel that too.</p>\n<p>This summer, Maxway will produce a limited run of 30 framesets, priced at $2000 for a frameset. If interested, reach out and join the <a href=\"https://www.maxway-cycles.com/contact.html\" target=\"_blank\">waitlist.</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/angels-maxway-cycles-zephyrus-road/\">Angel’s Maxway Cycles Zephyrus Road Bike: Steel, Coffee, Clay</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"spencer harding","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"8f2737d7b9dfab1f6652b8b06596228163a7b7396e4e48e52847be2614f6a303","category":"Cycling"}